10/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Directorate General for Emergency Management announced on Sunday (August 9th) that Turkey will treat 40 victims of Friday's bombing near Mosul. 
The attack, near a Shiite mosque in the village of al-Shelikan, killed 38 people and injured another 267. 
Ankara also pledged to donate food to help residents of Mosul, which is near Turkey's southeastern border. 
(Anadolu news agency, Xinhua - 09/08/09)
